727176f-b.text:
(1) - (2)
Laurel Hill Blvd (along front of buildings; not shown in this view), east of 58th Place (left not shown), showing a rear view of the Thomas H. Betts homestead in 1852. E.L. Ambruster states that this property belonged to one Erb at a later date. In 1909 it was owned by one Kelso. It is possible that one of the outbuildings on the south side of Laurel Hill Road opposite 58th Lane still stands.

May 1923
Views 1 & 2
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.

(3) The same, showing an additional barn.

May 1923.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
